A BOOZING spree has cost a young adult 12 years of his life.Mpumelelo Mlondo (20) from Msunduzi, KZN Midlands has been sentenced to 12 years behind bars for raping a woman he had been drinking with in his vehicle in June 2012.Mlondo was sentenced on Tuesday by the Camperdown Regional Court for a rape charge he committed at Othwebe in Msunduzi.KZN cops spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said that evening at about 9.30pm, the victim and her friend were at a tavern when they contacted Mlondo to fetch them. &ldquo;The accused, victim and her friend were drinking in the vehicle. &ldquo;After they finished that alcohol, the accused suggested that they all go to the nearest tavern to buy more liquor.On their way to the tavern the accused grabbed the victim and dragged her to the nearest bush,&rdquo; said Zwane.He said the victim tried to escape but the accused chased and assaulted her before eventually raping her. &ldquo;A case of rape was opened at Msunduzi Police Station and the docket was transferred to the Pinetown Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences unit for further investigation, that led to the arrest of the accused. &ldquo;He made several court appearances before he was convicted and sentenced.&rdquo;KZN acting provincial commissioner, Major-General Bheki Langa commended the sentencing and also applauded the police for their good work.